<div class="title">
<div class="quote-controls"></div>
<img loading="lazy" alt="" width="24" height="24" src="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/aronrubin/48/180072_2.png" class="avatar"> AronRubin:</div>
<blockquote>
<p>What are the limitations of using codespaces for robot development?</p>
</blockquote>
</aside>
<p>I believe these are the key limitations:</p>
<ul>
<li>no simulation GUI (although it may be possible to get there with VNC?)</li>
<li>no ability to deploy to the robot</li>
<li>no ability to talk to coprocessors</li>
<li>no driver station</li>
<li>no other GUI tools (dashboards, etc) (but maybe with VNC?)</li>
</ul>
